Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo The National Chairman of the Action Alliance, Mr Kenneth Udeze, on Monday appeared before the Osun State Magistrates’ Court in Osogbo, where he was charged with four counts of forgery, alteration and conspiracy. The prosecutor, Mr James Famuyimi, told the court that Udeze and some persons still at large forged a document and presented it to the Independent National Electoral Commission. He said the forged document was presented to INEC during AA’s governorship primary election in 2018. Famuyimi said Udeze violated Section 516 of the Criminal Code Cap 34, Voll 2, Laws of Osun State 2002 and was liable to be punished under Section 467 of the same law. But Udeze pleaded not guilty to the charges. Following an oral bail application by his lawyer, Wemimo Animasahun, the court admitted Udeze to bail in the sum of N200,000 with two sureties in like sum. The matter was adjourned till November 5, 2019 for mention. Copyright PUNCH.
